Prostomium subtriangular, with two annulations (border of annulations at anterior end of nuchal organs); much wider than long (ratio length / width: 0.94), anterior margin truncated (
Figs 39C
; 
40A
), with two intradermal eyes. Crown like ciliary band (clcb) present, but short ciliated slits (cs) above nuchal organs absent (
Fig. 40B
). Antenna short, digitiform, weakly bulbous, with a rounded tip, hardly reaching posterior margin of prostomium, inserted in mid-region of prostomium (
Figs 39C
; 
40B
). A pair of nuchal organs as narrow deep, short slits placed on dorsolateral sides of posterior prostomium, more or less convex in shape; dense internal ciliation present, cilia not reaching outer margin of slits; without pigmentation; a pair of ridges located in inner side of nuchal slits (
Figs 39C
; 
40B
). Mouth with three buccal lips; two placed anteriorly, one placed posteriorly extending to anterior margin of chaetiger 1, with eight longitudinal folds; a Y-shaped gap present between anterior lips (
Fig. 39B
).

Interramal lobes and notopodial papilla absent. Ventral lobes present on chaetigers 3–19, short, tuberculated (
Fig. 39G
).
